<br>
I see your point Anterak, but I'm talking about the DT every 2 and a half hours or so, which is double the time for a MB.<br>
<br>
In that time, a wizard could dish out 2 mana burns, thats 34k damage provided it does the full 17k like I assume it does.<br>
<br>
Yes, there are things that can go wrong, but on a perfect day (not that they come along every day) a wizard can dish out a hell of a lot of damage.<br>
<br>
We other classes dont have that luxury, but other classes do have features that make them useful on raids.<br>
<br>
Warriors - Obviously, they tank.<br>
Druids - Resists, Nukes, heals.<br>
Clerics - Obviously, they heal.<br>
Shaman - Slows, Debuffs, Heals, DoTs and occasionally Nukes<br>
Beastlord - ...ummm...ok maybe not ALL classes <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Enchanters - Haste, Mana recovery, memwipe, mez, Direcharm, etc.<br>
Bard - Resists, Manasong, regen, haste, etc.<br>
Monk - Massive damage dealing in small spaces of time<br>
Rogue - Massive damage dealing in small spaces of time<br>
Paladin - LoH, healing wave, etc.<br>
Necromancer - DoTs, tough as nails pet, mana feeding, direcharm of undead mobs, etc.<br>
Mage - DD's, Coth, tough as nails pets for different situations, modrods, etc.<br>
Wizard - Nukes, nukes, nukes and more nukes, Manaburn.<br>
<br>
All these classes are vital in their own ways and can help make or break a raid. Shadowknights, while being a very good class that I enjoy immensely, are underpowered compared to the rest of the classes.<br>
<br>
Shadowknight - 338 point lifetap (what good is that when you have 5k+ buffed hp on a raid?), weak dots (that dont stack if a necro is at the raid), AC and ATK taps (our only saving grace in my eyes), and of course Harm touch.<br>
<br>
HT with disc does 1501 damage at level 60, without disc it does 1001. While being quite good for grouping situations (there's nothing better than HTing a mob thats running, low on hp and about to aggro a whole hoard of mobs that could potentially wipe your group out) it's basically quite useless anywhere else, especially with its extreme 72 minute reuse time. <br>
<br>
On raids, I find that it gets resisted quite a bit(A lot less than it did pre 60, but still resisted), which leads me to believe that on 50 percent or so of the bossmobs in the game, we're pretty much useless against them. On some boss mobs, I cant HT, I cant ATK or AC tap, I cant lifetap and I manage to slash for roughly 80 damage per swing with a Primal Velium Axe due to our ridiculously low caps for melee weapons that Verant so graciously adorned us with.<br>
<br>
In groups, as I said previously, HT can save our asses on occasion. However, when you HT a mob with disc, that 1501 damage is roughly a 10th of what most luclin mobs have for HP, and HT that lands for 1501 damage will roughly knock 4 pixels or so of HP off of the Xin Thall Centiens in Maidens Eye. <br>
<br>
See my point now? Our only outstanding skill is still way underpowered compared to a single wizard nuke.<br>
<br>
I recently saw Brollan, a guildie (/wave Brollan <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), nuke for 4097 with a crit blast, thats four times the amount of damage that my HT does that I need to wait 72 minutes to use after each hit. Basically, if you consider the statistics, if Brollan nuked for 4000 damage and I only used Harmtouches (without disc), it would take me over 4 and a half hours to match up to the damage of a single nuke. With disc it'd still be just over 3 and a half hours to get 4500 damage. Sure I have my melee, I can slash up to 300 damage with my Ancient Fire Etched Flamberge, but on Luclin, with the ridiculously high AC that the mobs have (/poke Xerkizh the Creator) I dont stand much of a chance of hitting over 100 (average of around 40 damage per hit, yay me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
I can only imagine what PoP will be like if they decide to increase the AC and HP of mobs yet again without seriously considering the implications of it like they did with Luclin.<br>
<br>
And dont even get me started on Dark Empathy! a 20 hp heal! I believe the comic book store owner on the League of Gentlemen said it best when he said:<br>
<br>
&quot;Well whoopie shit...&quot;<br>
<br>
Must...massage...brain....nnnghh!<br>
<br>
